text]- ELTS will focus on patient and donor education.<\/p>\n<p>&#8211; Society will promote and spread knowledge in the community about liver diseases and screening investigations.<\/p>\n<p>&#8211; ELTS will work on living liver donor protection programs.<\/p>\n<p>&#8211; ELTS will help in establishment of deceased donor organ transplantation in Egypt.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Education and Training Committee&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1649215192261-c10493c5-36f2&#8243;][vc_column_text]- Educational Webinars<br \/>\n&#8211; Educational courses and workshops<br \/>\n&#8211; Development of Liver Transplant Training Curriculum in different related specialties.<br \/>\n&#8211; Delegated specialist members to work with other ELTS committees to develop relevant content for sessions in the ELTS Annual Congress.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;ELTS Executive Committee&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1659460675371-c93bcec2-1a17&#8243;][vc_column_text]The Egyptian Liver Transplantation Society is an organization dedicated to advancing the field of liver transplantation and improving patient care by promoting international outreach, research, education, advocacy, organ donation, and service to the community.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;International Outreach Committee&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1649215249687-3ff282da-1644&#8243;][vc_column_text]ELTS will work on establishment of strong connections with all recognized international societies in the field of transplantation and to make our society an official part of the international societies.<\/p>\n<p>\u2022 Establishment of international fellowships in Egypt.<\/p>\n<p>\u2022 Development of exchange programs for trainees and faculty.<\/p>\n<p>\u2022 Holding an annual congress under umbrella of international societies.<\/p>\n<p>\u2022 Work with executive committee to build up liver transplant programs in underserved areas.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Membership Committee&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1649215297260-dece4df2-cc8e&#8221;][vc_column_text]-Encourage all interested physicians, allied healthcare professionals to join ELTS membership.<\/p>\n<p>-Promote benefits of membership<\/p>\n<p>-Supervise Elections with board of trustees.<\/p>\n<p>&#8211; Supervise membership directory.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Marketing and Finance committee&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1649215299912-0ca58a03-c6d6&#8243;][vc_column_text]-Responsible for media promotions and fundraising from different funding bodies.<\/p>\n<p>-Ensures long term financial support of the society, give advises on management of the Fund for Education and other activities.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Research and Guidelines Committee&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1649214878150-c6a58e27-b627&#8243;][vc_column_text]Research remains a priority for the ELTS, with a focus on funding research that is innovative and unique.<\/p>\n<p>\u2022 ELTS will advocate for a liver transplant-specific study section through the Science, Technology, and Innovation Funding Authority (STDF), Egyptian Knowledge Bank (EKB) and Ministry of Higher Education and Scientific Research.<\/p>\n<p>\u2022 Building a network of expert centers dedicated to research in the area of liver transplantation.<\/p>\n<p>\u2022 Work with experts in the liver transplantation community for development of guidelines and consensus recommendations related to all aspects of liver transplantation.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Pediatrics Committee&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1649215404284-4d3de7f2-7dff&#8221;][vc_column_text]Pediatrics Committee is composed of experts with relevant backgrounds, skills, and experience in the field of pediatric liver transplantation.<\/p>\n<p>&#8211; Responsible for promoting and managing all activities related to pediatric liver transplantation.<\/p>\n<p>&#8211; Support educational and research activities related to pediatric liver transplantation[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Pathology and Radiology Committee&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1649215427143-ced4ef15-1567&#8243;][vc_column_text]- Responsible for raising standards of clinical care through ensuring the proper usage, application and interpretation of diagnostic modalities related to liver transplantation (pathology and radiology).<\/p>\n<p>&#8211; Preparing for ELTS congress sessions and workshops related to Radiology and Pathology<\/p>\n<p>&#8211; Educational Webinars and Workshops[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Vanguard Committee&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1649215275113-ca4d0c9a-ed72&#8243;][vc_column_text]This committee\u2019s mission is to promote the participation of younger members of the liver transplant community in all ELTS activities, and to guide the society in responding to their educational and professional needs.<\/p>\n<p>\u2013 Ascertain the educational and professional needs of younger members through informal discussion and the annual member survey, and work with the ELTS leadership to address these needs.<\/p>\n<p>\u2013 Recognizes and honors ELTS junior members for their efforts in basic and clinical research<\/p>\n<p>\u2013 Support young investigators\u2019 research activities[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][\/vc_tta_accordion][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column][vc_empty_space][vc_tta_accordion style=&#8221;flat&#8221; spacing=&#8221;10&#8243; c_icon=&#8221;triangle&#8221; active_section=&#8221;0&#8243; collapsible_all=&#8221;true&#8221; el_class=&#8221;Committees&#8221;][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Advocacy Committee&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1649214878144-d209b6ff-f512&#8243;][vc_column_text]The ELTS advocacy plan includes increasing collaboration with other professional national societies, engaging groups outside of our core